<br>
They are what gave me my world to grow up in.  I was a little nerdy kid.  Not many friends.  Speech impediment...glasses...braces, and damn if my parents didn't dress me funny!!<br>
<br>
These books were my escape.  The table top game Dungeon's and Dragons was great, but nothing like self imagination of diving into a book.  Ever since I was that age, I have been able to imagine myself in various roles.  I spent much of my night time activities reading in my room.  I had several friends, but none seemed to read as much as I did.  Poor lost souls!! haha<br>
<br>
Years past.  The Dragonlance series are still to this day my favorite fantasy reading.  I would always stop and gaze on fantasy art and the like at the hobby stores.  I never lost that part of me.  Again, not many around me understood my love for fantasy.  It was my way to escape stress and to be something I could never be in real life.<br>
<br>
Everquest came to be.  I read about it.  It had been out probably a year when I finally bought the game.  Wise investment.<br>
<br>
To those of you that play the game and love fantasy as much as I do, I salute and bow to you.  You are my brethren.<br>
<br>
To those of you who are able to share the game with loved ones, Neao and his daughter come to mind, as do Gwion and Aganitte..I cheer for you.  I have been trying to get my girlfriend online with me.  She ain't having it.  She just rolls her eyes when she sees me playing the game and gives me that quarky smile of hers.  Would be cool to see her in all leather..hehehe<br>
<br>
When I explain my reasoning for the love of the game, my words fall short.  I can't seem to get my point across.  I know that deep down, it was my need for escape that has built this need for fantasy and in the end, the love of this game and my guild.<br>
<br>
To those of you who are younger and love the game...read.  For those that are older and love the game...read.<br>
If someone were to ask me what they could do to prepare themselves for the worlds that lie ahead.  I would say read.  Imagination is king. <br>
<br>
Escape reality while you can.  <br>
<br>
Uriel Trueshot<br>
27th Woodie Ranger<br>
